The HTML DOM and JavaScript 
The HTML DOM (Document Object Model) is a structured representation of a web page created by the browser. It allows JavaScript to access, modify, add, or delete HTML elements dynamically, making webpages interactive.

What is the DOM?

DOM represents the webpage as a tree of objects
Each HTML element becomes a node/object
JavaScript can interact with these objects

<html>
 ├── <head>
 └── <body>
      ├── <h1>
      └── <p>

Why DOM is Important
Enables dynamic webpage updates
Allows user interaction handling
Helps create responsive interfaces
Makes websites behave like applications

How JavaScript Uses the DOM

JavaScript can:

✔ Change text content
✔ Change styles
✔ Add/remove elements
✔ Respond to user events (click, input, hover)